Key Match Events: Khama Billiat scored the winning penalty for Zimbabwe in the 34th minute.
Edward Maova made three saves for Namibia but could not stop the penalty.
Namibia hit the woodwork multiple times but failed to score.
Washington Arubi made five saves to keep a clean sheet for Zimbabwe.
Post-Match Reflections: Collin Benjamin praised his team's spirited performance despite the loss.
Michael Nees guided Zimbabwe to their first three points of the campaign and top place in the points table.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Zimbabwe extends their unbeaten run in the African Cup of Nations 2025 qualifiers.
